pages on demand.

00:44:43.500 --> 00:44:46.900
So, if they don't have a
common reference frame,

00:44:46.900 --> 00:44:51.120
reference terminology, and
reference space, that won't work.

00:44:51.120 --> 00:44:53.070
And so, I keep thinking,
that Google,

00:44:53.070 --> 00:44:55.490
you know does this sharding
thing where we take objects

00:44:55.490 --> 00:44:58.650
and we break them all up and
