00:52:29.410 --> 00:52:34.320 position:56%
So, the first thing is that this
digital object architecture uses the

00:52:34.320 --> 00:52:35.670
term handle system.

00:52:35.670 --> 00:52:37.950
Its handles are kind
of like domain names.

00:52:37.950 --> 00:52:41.010
They're references
to digital objects.

00:52:41.010 --> 00:52:46.000
And once you have this handle, when
you resolve it, it takes you to,

00:52:46.000 --> 00:52:47.900
or points you to that
digital object.

00:52:47.900 --> 00:52:50.420 position:56%
So, the handle is a permanent thing.

00:52:50.420 --> 00:52:52.670
That's a sign, it doesn't
get changed.

00:52:52.670 --> 00:52:54.790
Never gets reassigned
to anything else.

00:52:54.790 --> 00:52:56.870
And in theory doesn't disappear.

00:52:56.870 --> 00:52:58.520
This stuff is in use.

00:52:58.520 --> 00:53:02.040
So, I am not speculating at
this point, I am telling you

00:53:02.040 --> 00:53:05.440
about something which is
actually functioning and in use

00:53:05.440 --> 00:53:08.880
and you can see a list here,
which I won't read to you.

00:53:08.880 --> 00:53:12.640
So, the important part
here is that stuff

00:53:12.640 --> 00:53:14.440
that works is really important.

00:53:14.440 --> 00:53:16.660
I mean it's sort of
like the internet.

00:53:16.660 --> 00:53:18.710
Things that work persist.

00:53:18.710 --> 00:53:20.830
And I'm hoping that the
handle system will have

00:53:20.830 --> 00:53:23.080
that property as well.

00:53:23.080 --> 00:53:25.440
So, there's pieces
in this architecture.

00:53:25.440 --> 00:53:27.620
There's the client that's
trying to get access

00:53:27.620 --> 00:53:30.880
to an object by way of a handle.

00:53:30.880 --> 00:53:34.140
There is discovering what
resources are available

00:53:34.140 --> 00:53:35.600
down in the lower left.

00:53:35.600 --> 00:53:37.110
You know where can I go?

00:53:37.110 --> 00:53:38.950
In order to get things.

00:53:38.950 --> 00:53:41.190
Where, how do I find something?

00:53:41.190 --> 00:53:46.180
So, I need a resolution system
in the lower right for you.

00:53:46.180 --> 00:53:48.680
And then finally, you
want to go to a place

00:53:48.680 --> 00:53:50.190
where the objects are located.

00:53:50.190 --> 00:53:54.100
And so, this very simple,
conceptual architecture made

00:53:54.100 --> 00:53:57.370
up of these four components.

00:53:57.370 --> 00:53:59.500
So, here's an object.

00:53:59.500 --> 00:54:02.040
It's in the architecture.

00:54:02.040 --> 00:54:04.980
The digital object is
in the architecture

00:54:04.980 --> 00:54:08.770
as a first-class citizen
in the internet.

00:54:08.770 --> 00:54:13.030
So, the notion of digital object
becomes a first-class concept.

00:54:13.030 --> 00:54:16.360
So, we want to be able to
take these objects as objects,

00:54:16.360 --> 00:54:19.120
move them around, store
them away, recover them,

00:54:19.120 --> 00:54:21.160
interpret them, and so on.

00:54:21.160 --> 00:54:23.280 position:56%
These things could be quite complex.

00:54:23.280 --> 00:54:25.620
They can have all different
kinds of content in them.

00:54:25.620 --> 00:54:28.300
Could be video, could be
audio, could be a mix of that.

00:54:28.300 --> 00:54:30.110
Could be executables.

00:54:30.110 --> 00:54:32.870
Virtually anything you
can digitize should be,

00:54:32.870 --> 00:54:36.040
you know implementable
as a digital object.

00:54:36.040 --> 00:54:40.060 position:56%
And the whole idea behind the handle
system is that it helps you find

00:54:40.060 --> 00:54:43.250
